item.title: Eclipse
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“Resent, post:2, topic:431627”][quote author=superwiz789 link=topic=534333.msg3906393#msg3906393 date=1328269926]
Everytime I try and add a 562 source in my eclipse, it says “Project … is missing the required library Search.jar” and it won’t build the project. Can anyone help?
[/quote]

You’re trying to fit a 562 source with a different based client. You need to find a compatible client with your source.[/quote]

No.

The problem is that in Eclipse, you can add other projects and jars as dependencies for the current project. In your case, you’re missing “Search.jar” from your build path.
